"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-supersport-continue-to-frustrate-with-annoying-ads-during-paris-olympics-2024-breaking-exclusive\", \"text\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.  thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbSuperSport continue to frustrate with annoying ADS during Paris Olympics  Swimming fans were left tearing their hair out for the third day on Mondday as SuperSport cut to adverts, missing the results of events.  Paris Olympics 2024swimmingfans were left tearing their hair out for thethirdday running on Monday morning asSuperSportinsisted on cutting to adverts, missing the all-important final results of events.  Enjoy the Paris Olympic Games 2024 experience at your favourite ATKV Resort!  While it's one thing to watch a race, the times posted by the swimmers is all that matters in terms of progressing to the semi-finals - or directly to the final.  For the latest Paris Olympics 2024 news, bookmarkThe South African website'sdedicated section for free-to-read content  However, immediately after the final heat of each event, SuperSport insisted on cutting to advert breaks, thus denying viewers the opportunity of seeing the overall results.  The advert breaks frequently lasted so long that viewers missed the entrants walking out for the following event, often only seeing them when on the starting blocks.  One can only hope someone has a quiet word - or reads this article - and does something about the matter!  Come on, SuperSport, you are better than that!  For the millions of viewers who actuallyDOwant to see the results, they are urged to clickHERE- or better still, visitThe South African websitefor all the latest Paris Olympics 2024 news.  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring! Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's WhatsApp channel for the latest sport, lifestyle and local news  Follow The South African on X for the latest, breaking news  A brand new shopping mall is coming to Pretoria East, bringing major retailers and new convenience to the area.  Orlando Pirates are reportedly set to welcome a new staff member in former Stellenbosch FC Head of Recruitment Brendon Fourie.  Masindi Nemtajela was stretched off during Orlando Pirates' 6-0 win over TS Galaxy on Sunday afternoon in Mbombela.  IT support is not just technical, it is personal.  Liema Pantsi's victory was clouded as fans of the 'Big Brother Mzansi' show expressed that Smash Afrika was unprofessional towards her.  A dominant weekend for the SA teams in the URC has made a big impact on the latest log standings as the playoffs edge closer.    TheSouthAfrican.com is all about South Africa and the stories that affect South Africans, wherever they are in the world.  We are independent.No agenda.No bias.  Our offices are for administrative purposes only, no visitors will be accepted without an appointment.  South Africa- Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd - Registration Number: 2005/028472/07 - Address: Regus Business Centre, 1st Floor, Block B, North Park, Black River Park, 2 Fir Street, Observatory, Cape Town, 7925, South Africa  Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\"}"